Eskom recently announced in a statement that the grid is under severe strain and they will commence with stage two loadshedding in certain parts of the country. According to the Eskom loadshedding app, Middelburg will not be affected, however, the Middelburg Mall, Twizza and surrounds will be without electricity from 19:00. Residents have been notified to prepare for the possibility of loadshedding and have been urged to use electricity sparingly, to prevent further strain on the system. 